  <!-- 7. Internal Storage -->
  <h2 id="internal-storage" class="scroll-mt-20">Internal Storage</h2>
  <p>Q-Tune has 8MB of internal storage for custom standby images and set list files. Files can be managed via <a href="#usb-drive-mode">USB Drive Mode</a> or the <a href="#wifi-server">Wi-Fi Server</a>.</p>

  <h3>Custom Images</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Place JPEG and animated GIF files in the <code>standby/</code> folder</li>
    <li>Supported resolutions: <strong>320&times;240</strong> (landscape) or <strong>240&times;320</strong> (portrait)</li>
    <li>Smaller file sizes mean faster load times — keep images optimized for the best experience</li>
    <li>The <a href="/image-tools/">Image Tools</a> page can resize and convert your images, and includes a GIF optimizer that reduces the color palette and file size</li>
    <li>This is a DIY tuner — experimentation is encouraged! Try different images and GIFs to make your pedal your own</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Set Lists</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Place plain text <code>.txt</code> files in the <code>setlists/</code> folder</li>
    <li>One song title per line</li>
    <li>The display automatically adjusts the font size based on how many songs are in each file</li>
    <li>Experiment with the number of lines per file for the best results on your screen</li>
  </ul>

  <!-- 8. USB Drive Mode -->
  <h2 id="usb-drive-mode" class="scroll-mt-20">USB Drive Mode</h2>
  <p>USB Drive Mode lets you access Q-Tune's internal storage directly from your computer, just like a USB flash drive. Use it to add or remove custom images and set list files.</p>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Hold the footswitch</strong> while plugging in the USB-C cable (or while powering on the pedal via USB).</li>
    <li>The screen will display a USB Drive Mode indicator.</li>
    <li>The pedal will appear as a removable drive on your computer.</li>
    <li>Copy files to the <code>standby/</code> and <code>setlists/</code> folders as described in the <a href="#internal-storage">Internal Storage</a> section.</li>
    <li>Eject the drive and unplug the cable. The pedal will restart with the new files loaded.</li>
  </ol>

  <!-- 9. Wi-Fi Server -->
  <h2 id="wifi-server" class="scroll-mt-20">Wi-Fi Server</h2>
  <p>Q-Tune can run a built-in Wi-Fi server that lets you manage images, set lists, and settings from any device with a web browser — no cables required.</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Open <a href="#settings">Settings</a> and navigate to the <strong>Advanced</strong> page.</li>
    <li>Tap <strong>Wi-Fi Server</strong> to start.</li>
    <li>The pedal will create a Wi-Fi access point. The screen will display the network name and password.</li>
    <li>Connect your phone or computer to that Wi-Fi network.</li>
    <li>Open a web browser and go to the address shown on the pedal's screen.</li>
    <li>Use the web interface to upload/delete images, manage set lists, and adjust settings.</li>
    <li>When finished, tap <strong>Wi-Fi Server</strong> in Settings to set it to <strong>Stop</strong>. The tuner will reboot with all your changes to images and set lists ready to use.</li>
  </ol>

  <!-- 10. Firmware Updates -->
  <h2 id="firmware-updates" class="scroll-mt-20">Firmware Updates</h2>
  <p>Q-Tune firmware can be updated directly from your browser using a USB-C data cable. No special software is required.</p>
  <ol>
    <li>Go to the <a href="/install/">Install</a> page on this website and follow the instructions.</li>
    <li>Connect your Q-Tune to your computer with a USB-C data cable.</li>
    <li>Click the <strong>Install</strong> button and follow the on-screen prompts.</li>
    <li>The firmware will be flashed to your pedal. Once complete, the pedal will restart automatically.</li>
  </ol>
  <p>Your settings, custom images, and set lists are preserved during firmware updates unless you select the Erase option.</p>
</PageLayout>

